task.summary:
PACKAGES: - Made an enum folder to hold genre enums. - Created another module folder to hold test classes
BUDGETER CLASS: - Added more user functionality to choosing transaction values, descriptions, and genres. - Commented out load/save functionality to implement later
REVGENRE/EXPGENRE CLASSES: - gave each enum case a lower case string form attribute - added a static method that can print out all cases in the respective enum
EXPENSE/REVENUE CLASSES - Revenue and Expense extend from Transaction
NEW CLASSES - Transaction (abstract class) - Command Handler (class): going to hold commandHandler methods that will take in user input and execute actions - Prompter (class): contains methods that prompts and return different types of user input

Budgeter now has a list of Entries instead of a list of Transactions. All commands revolve around dealing with Entries now (addEntry, viewEntries, etc)
Moved addRevenue/Expense functionality to the Entry class, where all commands dealing with Transactions are in Entry now
Created a SimpleDate class.

Fixed recursive bug in promptMoreTransactions.
Changed Expense and Revenue toStrings

Commit before complete refactor of program.
Attempting to separate UI functionality from the program model/data/behaviour functionality.

Implemented EntryPrompter class.
Added Exception throwing to methods that add a given parameter to a list.
Created a singleton Prompter class that provides scanner return methods.

Made enums a subtype of a higher supertype, allowing for majoring refactoring to occur between Transaction, Revenue, and Expense.
Added EntrySearchManager and TransactionGenreManager classes as a means to store transactions in a set/map, but will probably delete later as a hashmap may not be necessary for my program.
Added invalid date exceptions to the date class.

Made enums a subtype of a higher supertype, allowing for majoring refactoring to occur between Transaction, Revenue, and Expense.
Added EntrySearchManager and TransactionGenreManager classes as a means to store transactions in a set/map, but will probably delete later as a hashmap may not be necessary for my program.
Added invalid date exceptions to the date class.
Created setters for TransactionManager and Transaction that properly establish and remove bi-directional associations
Removed UI functionality (i.e. print statements) from enums RevGenre and ExpGenre, making methods return strings instead

Refactored SimpleDate class to hold a Calendar object. As well, added two static classes to help with retrieving date symbols and date formatting. SimpleDate class should be moved into new "date" folder, however, it becomes marked red and the reason why is unknown.
